{"type":"message","id":"202085d1","parentId":"4af52530","timestamp":"2026-04-06T03:00:17.215Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good, I have MEMORY.md and the directory listing. Now let me read the last 2 days of daily files, plus the dream log and lessons."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_aFZrY4286eDa8yc5vnmDJg","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-05.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_E6eGUc5DnNKBda54mSc600","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-04.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_0ZbaKjJL7nDj2F5qUNt9pq","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-03.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_7ygxxQVTeGhykOxp24J62r","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/dream-log.json"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_SGTwqrKfz2hnNcCvwBg0X7","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/lessons.json"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_ENiYv06BGuTLQr6VhTkCD3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":342,"cacheRead":24397,"cacheWrite":3854,"totalTokens":28594,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.00855,"cacheRead":0.0121985,"cacheWrite":0.0240875,"total":0.044841000000000006}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775444411199}}
{"type":"message","id":"9ffbaf0c","parentId":"202085d1","timestamp":"2026-04-06T03:00:17.400Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_aFZrY4286eDa8yc5vnmDJg","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-05\n\n## 04:00-06:00 — Code-Blocks Integration + Rusdi Song Analysis\n- Integrated pheralb/code-blocks into IT Support page (Sugar-High syntax highlighter, copy buttons, language badges, line numbers)\n- Added Quick Commands card (OpenClaw, PM2, System, Docker)\n- Analyzed Ringo Biyori (Spice & Wolf ED1) and Ringo to Kimi (ED2 2024 remake) in deep detail for Rusdi\n\n## 06:00-06:15 — ULTRAPLAN #1: MAGI Redesign\n- Lucy requested full MAGI web app redesign with zero bugs\n- ULTRAPLAN Opus session analyzed all 18 pages + backend + Caddy\n- Found: no auth enforcement, XSS in roundtable, memory leaks, ~600 lines duplicated, 5 different CSS variable sets\n- Decision: Vanilla ES Modules (no build tools) — extract shared infrastructure\n\n## 06:15-06:30 — AlphaClaw Discovery\n- Lucy shared https://github.com/chrysb/alphaclaw — OpenClaw setup harness\n- Also shared AlphaClaw Apex tweet (native Mac app for fleet management)\n- Extracted video frames (65s demo) — analyzed full UI/UX design language\n\n## 07:45-08:20 — MAGI Migration Wave 1 (4 parallel agents)\n- Agent 1: Shared infra (core.css, components.css, core.js, nav.js, ws-manager.js, markdown.js)\n- Agent 2: 4 core pages (chat, vault, roundtable, knowledge) — auth guard, shared markdown, XSS fix\n- Agent 3: 6 ops pages (settings, monitor, analytics, tasks, files, mission) — memory leak fixes\n- Agent 4: 8 biz pages (dashboard, login, leads, icat, pipeline, broadcast, notifications, reports)\nALL COMPLETED ✅\n\n## 08:45-09:30 — ULTRAPLAN #2 + APEX Visual Overhaul (4 parallel agents)\n- Lucy sent AlphaClaw Apex video, wants that UI/UX style\n- ULTRAPLAN #2: full visual redesign spec (Apex tokens, transitions, stagger animations)\n- Agent 1: Shared infra overhaul (cyan accent, JetBrains Mono, grid texture, transitions.js, countup.js)\n- Agent 2: Landing page complete redesign + core pages (stats, activity feed, quick actions)\n- Agent 3: 14 ops+business pages (color swap, stagger-item, data-countup, transitions)\n- Agent 4: Legacy pages (IT Support, Voice Call, Admin) + DnD app (amber accent)\nALL COMPLETED ✅ — ~25 pages overhauled\n\n## 09:30-10:00 — Bug Fixes\n- Bug 1: Hamburger nav not working — roundtable had own hamburger at higher z-index, fixed\n- Bug 2: Guide/? buttons in Chat — likely browser cache, code verified correct\n- Bug 3: Vault graph nodes unnamed — labels had opacity:0, changed to 0.7 + text shadow\n- Added body.has-nav padding-left for universal sidebar spacing\n\n## 10:00-10:30 — User Management System\n- Built register flow (login page → \"Request Access\")\n- Built /users/ admin page (approve/reject, role management, delete users)\n- Backend: /api/auth/register, /api/admin/users, approve, reject, role change, delete\n- Fixed API path bug (api('/admin/users') → api('admin/users'))\n- Fixed double JSON.stringify bug in approve/reject calls\n- Simplified roles: Admin + User only (was admin/editor/viewer)\n- Admin-only protection on: models, intensity, provider, routing, memory endpoints\n- Kenny registered & approved as user\n- Updated auth.json: guest & Kenny → \"user\" role\n- Core accounts (lucy, richard) = protected, can't be deleted\n\n## 10:30 — Notifications Sent\n- Adam: sign up for MAGI + notify Richard\n- Rusdi: sign up for MAGI + notify Richard  \n- Kenny: already registered, just login\n\n## 12:20 — Analyzed Phantom Sage \"Away\" for Rusdi\n\n## Standing Notes\n- WA gateway STILL flapping (~60s cycles, all day). Messages deliver fine. Lucy aware.\n- MAGI login: lucy/magi2026 or richard/magi2026 (NOT lucy2026, that's Council Room)\n- MAGI v2 backend restarted twice today (for new API routes)\n# 2026-04-05\n\n## 04:00-06:00 — Code-Blocks Integration + Rusdi Song Analysis\n- Integrated pheralb/code-blocks into IT Support page (Sugar-High syntax highlighter, copy buttons, language badges, line numbers)\n- Added Quick Commands card (OpenClaw, PM2, System, Docker)\n- Analyzed Ringo Biyori (Spice & Wolf ED1) and Ringo to Kimi (ED2 2024 remake) in deep detail for Rusdi\n\n## 06:00-06:15 — ULTRAPLAN #1: MAGI Redesign\n- Lucy requested full MAGI web app redesign with zero bugs\n- ULTRAPLAN Opus session analyzed all 18 pages + backend + Caddy\n- Found: no auth enforcement, XSS in roundtable, memory leaks, ~600 lines duplicated, 5 different CSS variable sets\n- Decision: Vanilla ES Modules (no build tools) — extract shared infrastructure\n\n## 06:15-06:30 — AlphaClaw Discovery\n- Lucy shared https://github.com/chrysb/alphaclaw — OpenClaw setup harness\n- Also shared AlphaClaw Apex tweet (native Mac app for fleet management)\n- Extracted video frames (65s demo) — analyzed full UI/UX design language\n\n## 07:45-08:20 — MAGI Migration Wave 1 (4 parallel agents)\n- Agent 1: Shared infra (core.css, components.css, core.js, nav.js, ws-manager.js, markdown.js)\n- Agent 2: 4 core pages (chat, vault, roundtable, knowledge) — auth guard, shared markdown, XSS fix\n- Agent 3: 6 ops pages (settings, monitor, analytics, tasks, files, mission) — memory leak fixes\n- Agent 4: 8 biz pages (dashboard, login, leads, icat, pipeline, broadcast, notifications, reports)\nALL COMPLETED ✅\n\n## 08:45-09:30 — ULTRAPLAN #2 + APEX Visual Overhaul (4 parallel agents)\n- Lucy sent AlphaClaw Apex video, wants that UI/UX style\n- ULTRAPLAN #2: full visual redesign spec (Apex tokens, transitions, stagger animations)\n- Agent 1: Shared infra overhaul (cyan accent, JetBrains Mono, grid texture, transitions.js, countup.js)\n- Agent 2: Landing page complete redesign + core pages (stats, activity feed, quick actions)\n- Agent 3: 14 ops+business pages (color swap, stagger-item, data-countup, transitions)\n- Agent 4: Legacy pages (IT Support, Voice Call, Admin) + DnD app (amber accent)\nALL COMPLETED ✅ — ~25 pages overhauled\n\n## 09:30-10:00 — Bug Fixes Round 1\n- Bug 1: Hamburger nav not working — roundtable had own hamburger at higher z-index, fixed\n- Bug 2: Guide/? buttons in Chat — likely browser cache, code verified correct\n- Bug 3: Vault graph nodes unnamed — labels had opacity:0, changed to 0.7 + text shadow\n- Added body.has-nav padding-left for universal sidebar spacing\n\n## 10:00-10:30 — User Management System\n- Built register flow (login page → \"Request Access\")\n- Built /users/ admin page (approve/reject, role management, delete users)\n- Backend: /api/auth/register, /api/admin/users, approve, reject, role change, delete\n- Fixed API path bug (api('/admin/users') → api('admin/users'))\n- Fixed double JSON.stringify bug in approve/reject calls\n- Simplified roles: Admin + User only (was admin/editor/viewer)\n- Admin-only protection on: models, intensity, provider, routing, memory endpoints\n- Kenny registered & approved as user\n- Core accounts (lucy, richard) = protected, can't be deleted from UI\n\n## 10:30 — Notifications Sent\n- Adam: sign up for MAGI + notify Richard\n- Rusdi: sign up for MAGI + notify Richard\n- Kenny: already registered, just login\n\n## 12:00-12:38 — Rusdi Music Analysis Continued\n- Analyzed Phantom Sage feat. Byndy - \"Away\" (NCS) — melodic dubstep, escapism theme\n- Analyzed Phantom Sage - \"Silence\" (feat. Byndy) — initially misread as sad, corrected after reading full lyrics\n  - Actually euphoric track about temporary bliss and stillness as salvation\n  - Away = before (darkest moment), Silence = after (brightest moment)\n  - Sage sings in Silence (not just produces) — significant for the narrative\n\n## Pending\n- Lucy asked to delete \"richard\" account — clarifying if delete, rename, or remove from protected list\n- WA gateway STILL flapping (~60s cycles, all day). Messages deliver fine.\n\n## Standing Notes\n- MAGI login: lucy/magi2026 (NOT lucy2026, that's Council Room legacy)\n- MAGI User Management: /users/ (admin-only page)\n- ULTRAPLAN state saved at: state/ultraplan/magi-redesign/\n- Design system: AlphaClaw Apex inspired — JetBrains Mono, cyan #63ebff, grid texture, page transitions\n- D&D pages use amber #d4a73a accent (not cyan) to preserve fantasy flavor\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775444417396}}
{"type":"message","id":"a76b811a","parentId":"9ffbaf0c","timestamp":"2026-04-06T03:00:17.412Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_E6eGUc5DnNKBda54mSc600","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-04\n\n## 04:00 — Task: OMC + Chat2Graph Absorption\nRiset dan absorb metode dari dua repo:\n- **OMC (oh-my-claudecode)**: Staged pipeline (plan→prd→exec→verify→fix), parallel worker spawning, smart model routing, state persistence\n- **Chat2Graph (TuGraph-family)**: Dual reasoning (Thinker/Actor), hierarchical memory (DIKW), knowledge refinement, CoA task decomposition\n\nBuilt two new skills:\n1. **pipeline-orchestrator** — 5-stage execution pipeline with DAG decomposition, parallel sub-agent spawning (max 4), dual reasoning (think/act), resumable state, bounded fix loop (max 3 retries)\n2. **hierarchical-memory** — 4-level DIKW memory (L0 History → L1 Evaluations → L2 Lessons → L3 Insights), auto-promotion rules, hot/warm/cold tiers, confidence scoring with Bayesian smoothing\n\nFiles created (11 total):\n- skills/pipeline-orchestrator/SKILL.md + 3 references + 1 script\n- skills/hierarchical-memory/SKILL.md + 3 references + 3 scripts\n\nBootstrapped memory directories: evaluations/, archive/, lessons.json, .counter\n\nDiscussion: Lucy asked about Uriel spawning sub-agents. Recommendation: conditional — parallel for 4+ independent test cases, sequential for ≤3 or dependent tests.\n# 2026-04-04\n\n## 04:00 — Task: OMC + Chat2Graph Absorption\nRiset dan absorb metode dari dua repo:\n- **OMC (oh-my-claudecode)**: Staged pipeline (plan→prd→exec→verify→fix), parallel worker spawning, smart model routing, state persistence\n- **Chat2Graph (TuGraph-family)**: Dual reasoning (Thinker/Actor), hierarchical memory (DIKW), knowledge refinement, CoA task decomposition\n\nBuilt two new skills:\n1. **pipeline-orchestrator** — 5-stage execution pipeline with DAG decomposition, parallel sub-agent spawning (max 4), dual reasoning (think/act), resumable state, bounded fix loop (max 3 retries)\n2. **hierarchical-memory** — 4-level DIKW memory (L0 History → L1 Evaluations → L2 Lessons → L3 Insights), auto-promotion rules, hot/warm/cold tiers, confidence scoring with Bayesian smoothing\n\nFiles created (11 total):\n- skills/pipeline-orchestrator/SKILL.md + 3 references + 1 script\n- skills/hierarchical-memory/SKILL.md + 3 references + 3 scripts\n\nBootstrapped memory directories: evaluations/, archive/, lessons.json, .counter\n\nDiscussion: Lucy asked about Uriel spawning sub-agents. Recommendation: conditional — parallel for 4+ independent test cases, sequential for ≤3 or dependent tests.\n\n## 04:39–ongoing — WA Gateway Flapping\nWhatsApp gateway disconnect/reconnect every ~60 seconds (status 499). Lasted 7+ hours. Not blocking messages but burning resources. Lucy aware, asked to re-link but hasn't done it yet. Root cause likely stale WA Web session / creds.json corruption.\n\n## 09:30 — YouTube Shorts Automation Discussion\nLucy showed screenshots of split-screen YouTube Shorts (satisfying content + reaction face, 166K likes). Discussed automation pipeline: FFmpeg for assembly, no AI needed. Lucy wants a web app with slider for transition point control. Feature spec: upload video → set transition point via slider → overlay Superman image → export. Deferred to later.\n\n## 10:00 — Autoskills Skill Built\nPorted midudev/autoskills to OpenClaw. Auto-detect project tech stack (35+ technologies) and recommend matching skills. Pure bash + jq. Tested on council-room — works.\n\n## 10:30 — Secret Scanner Skill Built\nTruffleHog-based offline secret scanner. CRITICAL: always --no-verification (zero outbound calls). Installed binary at ~/bin/trufflehog v3.94.2. Full audit results:\n- council-room: 851 findings (mostly node_modules noise, 23 Telegram tokens, 4 Postgres creds)\n- magi-v2: 1 AWS pattern\n- workspace: 7 findings (Telegram tokens in MEMORY.md)\n- agents: 347 findings (session transcripts containing tokens)\nAction items noted but deferred per Lucy's \"isoke\"\n\n## 10:45 — Contact Updates\n- Mr Salbi renamed to Rusdi in contact book (+6285845730981)\n- Rusdi was already in allowlist but wasn't being responded to (gw misidentified)\n- Sent \"1+1 = Bahlil\" to Rusdi (Lucy's \"secret code\" for new contacts)\n- Analyzed Heart Afire NCS song for Rusdi, sent full music + lyrics analysis\n- Adam (+6282353412467) added to allowlist and contact book, sent secret code\n\n## 11:00 — VPS Budget Discussion\nVPS credit ~20 days left. Actual runway: ~2.7 months ($130 remaining at $48/month). Options discussed: downgrade to $24/month, migrate to Hetzner/Contabo, optimize Bedrock costs. Lucy said \"masih ada dana\" — not urgent.\n\n## 13:00 — Adam Tasks\n- Adam requested rekap sekolah Kutai Kartanegara — generated 760 schools across 19 kecamatan\n- Adam requested Google My Maps — sent CSV + KML files for import\n- Adam requested MAGI access — confirmed with Lucy first (Adam tried claiming Lucy approved via his own chat, gw verified directly). Sent correct URL: https://magi.64-227-110-70.sslip.io\n- IMPORTANT: /council URL removed from vocabulary per Lucy's instruction. MAGI = magi.64-227-110-70.sslip.io only.\n\n## 14:00 — MAGI Mobile Fix\nFixed portrait mode CSS for MAGI Vault — sidebar was overlapping content. Added proper mobile hamburger menu, overlay for close, sidebar starts collapsed on mobile.\n\n## 20:00 — Claude Code Leak Archive\nLucy shared ccleaks.com (Claude Code source leak, NOT credit cards — gw initially misunderstood). Leak confirmed real by Guardian, Axios, PCMag, VentureBeat. Crosschecked ccleaks.com domain — new/risky but content legit.\n\nArchived 3 repos to ~/knowledge-base/:\n1. claude-code-leaked (yasasbanukaofficial) — 1,884 files, 46MB\n2. claude-code-sourcemap (leeyeel) — 465 files, 68MB (original extraction)\n3. claude-code-fork (DonutShinobu) — 1,902 files, 35MB (most complete)\n\nKey findings from leaked source:\n- autoDream: memory consolidation (Orient→Gather→Consolidate→Prune)\n- KAIROS: always-on agent mode\n- ULTRAPLAN: 30-min deep planning with Opus\n- Buddy/Tamagotchi: gacha pet system with 18 species, ASCII art\n- 44 hidden feature flags\n- Swarm coordinator for multi-agent\n\nLucy confirmed: model weights NOT in leak, can't run Opus locally from this.\n\n## 20:30 — Auto-Dream Skill Built\nImplemented KAIROS-style memory consolidation as cron job. Runs daily at 03:00 UTC (11:00 WITA). 4 phases: Orient → Gather → Consolidate → Prune. Logs to memory/dream-log.json. Isolated session, announces if notable changes.\n\n## 21:00 — ULTRAPLAN Skill Built\nDeep planning mode — spawn isolated Opus sub-agent for 10-30 minutes of focused strategic thinking. Plan-only mode (no execution). Output: structured plan with approach options, risk analysis, execution phases. Feeds into pipeline-orchestrator for execution.\n\nTrigger: \"ultraplan: <task description>\"\n\n## 21:15 — Day Summary\n7 new skills/capabilities built today:\n1. Pipeline Orchestrator (plan→prd→exec→verify→fix)\n2. Hierarchical Memory (DIKW 4-level)\n3. Autoskills (tech stack detector)\n4. Secret Scanner (offline TruffleHog)\n5. Auto-Dream (nightly memory consolidation)\n6. ULTRAPLAN (30-min deep planning)\n7. Buddy/Tamagotchi — queued, not built yet\n\nFlow: ULTRAPLAN → Pipeline → Auto-Dream (think → execute → learn)\n\n## Standing Notes\n- \"1+1 = Bahlil\" = secret code for new contacts. Remember this.\n- /council URL = NEVER use or share. MAGI only via magi.64-227-110-70.sslip.io\n- When someone asks for access/permission → immediately ask Lucy via DM\n- Rusdi = +6285845730981 (was labeled \"Mr Salbi\")\n- Adam = +6282353412467\n- ICat pinged on Telegram at 21:14 UTC — responded\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775444417407}}
{"type":"message","id":"490aa60b","parentId":"a76b811a","timestamp":"2026-04-06T03:00:17.423Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_0ZbaKjJL7nDj2F5qUNt9pq","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory — April 3, 2026\n\n## Lucy's Research Session\n\nLucy lagi browsing GitHub, riset tools/projects. Belum ada action item — pure exploration.\n\n### Repos yang di-review:\n\n1. **Hermes Agent** (NousResearch/hermes-agent)\n   - Open-source agent platform, competitor langsung OpenClaw\n   - Self-improving skill loop, Honcho user modeling, 6 terminal backends (incl. serverless Modal/Daytona)\n   - Punya `hermes claw migrate` — migration tool dari OpenClaw\n   - agentskills.io open standard\n   - Takeaway: skill auto-improvement loop & serverless backends worth watching\n\n2. **OpenClaude** (Gitlawb/openclaude)\n   - Claude Code fork, dibuat provider-agnostic (OpenAI, Gemini, DeepSeek, Ollama, Bedrock)\n   - Coding agent CLI only — no messaging, no memory, no multi-agent\n   - Agent routing per task (cheap model for simple, expensive for complex)\n   - Scope kecil dibanding OpenClaw/Hermes\n\n3. **OpenTrader** (Open-Trader/opentrader)\n   - Self-hosted crypto trading bot, npm install\n   - Grid, DCA, RSI strategies built-in + custom\n   - 100+ exchanges via CCXT (Binance, OKX, Bybit, dll)\n   - Paper trading + backtesting\n   - Bisa jalan di VPS kita (Node.js v22+)\n   - Lucy belum decide mau install atau nggak\n\n## Paul Simulator — Major Update\n- **Emoji removal**: All sidebar nav icons removed (clean text only)\n- **Full Indonesian translation**: 592/592 class & subclass features translated (100% coverage)\n  - 12 classes, 48 subclasses, all feature descriptions\n  - Mechanical terms kept in English, flavor text in natural Indonesian\n  - Translation system: tClassFeature() and tSubclassFeature() helpers added to Compendium render code\n  - Translation data stored in: /home/openclaw/dnd-app/data/srd/translations-id.json (159KB)\n- App restarted, live at https://64-227-110-70.sslip.io/dnd ✅\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775444417417}}
