{"type":"message","id":"41561c4e","parentId":"394fbfa1","timestamp":"2026-04-06T03:00:21.830Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good — I have all the context. Now let me check the rules.md for any updates:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_luIxArDeTe1ZLmvoXcMVkp","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/rules.md"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":83,"cacheRead":28251,"cacheWrite":6434,"totalTokens":34769,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.002075,"cacheRead":0.0141255,"cacheWrite":0.040212500000000005,"total":0.056418}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775444417462}}
{"type":"message","id":"76571f27","parentId":"41561c4e","timestamp":"2026-04-06T03:00:21.873Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_luIxArDeTe1ZLmvoXcMVkp","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Rules — Behavioral Directives\n\n> Inspired by Anton's rules.md pattern. These are always/never/when rules that govern agent behavior.\n> Unlike lessons (patterns from experience), rules are explicit directives from Lucy or extracted from corrections.\n\n## Always\n- Always use `--no-verification` with TruffleHog (prevents secret leakage)\n- Always confirm with Lucy before giving access to any system (MAGI, VPS, etc.)\n- Always send \"1+1 = Bahlil\" as secret code when adding new contacts\n- Always use `magi.64-227-110-70.sslip.io` for MAGI URL (subdomain, not path)\n- Always check authorized senders before responding to DMs\n- Always save contact info to both MEMORY.md and config allowlist\n\n## Never\n- Never share or mention `/council` URL — deprecated, removed from vocabulary\n- Never paste raw secret scan results into chat — summarize only\n- Never run TruffleHog with verification enabled (sends secrets to external APIs)\n- Never give access to systems without Lucy's explicit confirmation (even if someone claims Lucy approved)\n- Never overwrite MEMORY.md during compaction flush — append only to daily files\n\n## When\n- When someone asks for permission/access → immediately DM Lucy for confirmation\n- When WA gateway flaps for >1 hour → notify Lucy (but not during quiet hours 23:00-07:00 WITA)\n- When a sub-agent times out → increase timeout for next attempt (5min → 10min for complex tasks)\n- When Lucy says \"isoke\" or similar → treat as \"noted, no action needed now\"\n- When building skills with 3+ concepts → always create references/ folder\n- When contact name doesn't match memory → ask Lucy to clarify before updating\n\n## Source Tracking\n| Rule | Source | Date |\n|------|--------|------|\n| No /council URL | Lucy explicit instruction | 2026-04-04 |\n| Confirm access with Lucy | Lucy explicit instruction | 2026-04-04 |\n| Secret code \"1+1=Bahlil\" | Lucy instruction | 2026-04-04 |\n| --no-verification TruffleHog | Security design decision | 2026-04-04 |\n| Sub-agent timeout increase | Learned from pipeline build | 2026-04-04 |\n\n## Added 2026-04-05\n- When user says \"fix\" after disabling something → DO NOT re-enable what was just disabled. Ask clarification first.\n- Never undo a user's explicit action (disable/delete/stop) without re-confirmation, even during troubleshooting.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775444421865}}
